00:44:56.630 --> 00:45:03.740 align:middle line:90%


00:45:03.740 --> 00:45:07.360 align:middle line:10%
NARRATOR>>After prolonged
stress or traumatic events,

00:45:07.360 --> 00:45:13.340 align:middle line:10%
or even a bad day, fear, anger,
and stress can become chronic

00:45:13.340 --> 00:45:17.470 align:middle line:10%
muscular tension
patterns in the body.

00:45:17.470 --> 00:45:21.430 align:middle line:84%
TRE is an innovative
physical technique

00:45:21.430 --> 00:45:24.160 align:middle line:84%
that enables the body
to naturally shake away

00:45:24.160 --> 00:45:29.140 align:middle line:84%
stress, safely unwind
buried tension while calming

00:45:29.140 --> 00:45:30.820 align:middle line:90%
the nervous system.

00:45:30.820 --> 00:45:34.760 align:middle line:84%
All this activated in an
intentional and controlled

00:45:34.760 --> 00:45:36.780 align:middle line:90%
manner.

00:45:36.780 --> 00:45:39.530 align:middle line:84%
As seen in the animal
kingdom, mammals

00:45:39.530 --> 00:45:43.820 align:middle line:84%
employ a tremor-like shaking
reflex to quickly calm down

00:45:43.820 --> 00:45:46.050 align:middle line:84%
the nervous system
after escaping

00:45:46.050 --> 00:45:50.680 align:middle line:84%
from perceived or real threats
or excessive excitement.

00:45:50.680 --> 00:45:53.010 align:middle line:10%
Many of us have
seen dogs or felt

00:45:53.010 --> 00:45:54.600 align:middle line:10%
dog shaking to calm themselves.

00:45:54.600 --> 00:46:02.220 align:middle line:90%


00:46:02.220 --> 00:46:04.780 align:middle line:84%
Much like a
pressure-release valve,

00:46:04.780 --> 00:46:09.510 align:middle line:84%
this same tension-releasing
mechanism exists in humans.

00:46:09.510 --> 00:46:13.532 align:middle line:84%
But culturally, we have
learned to suppress or override

00:46:13.532 --> 00:46:14.115 align:middle line:90%
this response.

00:46:14.115 --> 00:46:17.970 align:middle line:90%


00:46:17.970 --> 00:46:21.260 align:middle line:84%
Until now, it has not
been well-studied or

00:46:21.260 --> 00:46:23.680 align:middle line:90%
well-understood.

00:46:23.680 --> 00:46:28.090 align:middle line:10%
Dr. David Berceli, while working
in trauma and stress recovery

00:46:28.090 --> 00:46:31.970 align:middle line:10%
in war-torn areas, recognized
the healing potential

00:46:31.970 --> 00:46:37.550 align:middle line:10%
of this reflex for relieving
traumatic and chronic stress.

00:46:37.550 --> 00:46:43.070 align:middle line:10%
He developed TRE as a reliable
series of simple exercises

00:46:43.070 --> 00:46:46.700 align:middle line:10%
to help individuals activate
this reflex response

00:46:46.700 --> 00:46:50.180 align:middle line:10%
and to sustain it comfortably.

00:46:50.180 --> 00:46:54.220 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Berceli understood
an important paradox.

00:46:54.220 --> 00:46:57.360 align:middle line:84%
This tremor-like or
shaking reflex-- although

00:46:57.360 --> 00:47:02.240 align:middle line:84%
of an involuntary origin--
can be activated deliberately

00:47:02.240 --> 00:47:06.140 align:middle line:84%
to unwind muscle tension,
while calming and balancing

00:47:06.140 --> 00:47:09.220 align:middle line:90%
the nervous system.

00:47:09.220 --> 00:47:12.890 align:middle line:84%
When initiated in a safe
and controlled environment,

00:47:12.890 --> 00:47:17.220 align:middle line:84%
reflexive muscle vibration,
shaking, or tremoring

00:47:17.220 --> 00:47:22.860 align:middle line:84%
can feel remarkably effortless,
pleasant, and soothing.

00:47:22.860 --> 00:47:26.990 align:middle line:10%
Many people report feelings of
relief from deep-rooted stress

00:47:26.990 --> 00:47:30.510 align:middle line:10%
and tension that sometimes
cannot be achieved through

00:47:30.510 --> 00:47:34.800 align:middle line:10%
other methods such as
physical exercise, meditation,

00:47:34.800 --> 00:47:35.810 align:middle line:10%
or talk therapy.

00:47:35.810 --> 00:47:39.340 align:middle line:90%


00:47:39.340 --> 00:47:42.490 align:middle line:84%
Initially, simple
gentle exercises

00:47:42.490 --> 00:47:45.530 align:middle line:84%
will stretch specific
core muscles.

00:47:45.530 --> 00:47:48.840 align:middle line:84%
And then, a natural
tension-releasing reflex

00:47:48.840 --> 00:47:52.820 align:middle line:90%
can be intentionally initiated.

00:47:52.820 --> 00:47:57.160 align:middle line:10%
This mechanism creates
therapeutic muscle tremors

00:47:57.160 --> 00:47:59.590 align:middle line:10%
that can relieve tension
and be self-soothing.

00:47:59.590 --> 00:48:03.990 align:middle line:90%


00:48:03.990 --> 00:48:07.090 align:middle line:10%
With practice, these
therapeutic tremors

00:48:07.090 --> 00:48:09.610 align:middle line:10%
can be activated easily
and almost spontaneously.

00:48:09.610 --> 00:48:13.880 align:middle line:90%


00:48:13.880 --> 00:48:17.320 align:middle line:10%
With practice and
periodic use, most people

00:48:17.320 --> 00:48:21.990 align:middle line:10%
report that TRE helps release
deep-rooted tension, stress,

00:48:21.990 --> 00:48:23.550 align:middle line:10%
and trauma.

00:48:23.550 --> 00:48:26.450 align:middle line:10%
In many cases, they
have experienced results

00:48:26.450 --> 00:48:28.175 align:middle line:10%
that are often quite profound.

00:48:28.175 --> 00:48:34.470 align:middle line:90%


00:48:34.470 --> 00:48:37.200 align:middle line:84%
By simply adjusting
the leg positions,

00:48:37.200 --> 00:48:40.340 align:middle line:84%
the progression can easily
be paced and controlled.

00:48:40.340 --> 00:48:50.260 align:middle line:90%


00:48:50.260 --> 00:48:54.160 align:middle line:10%
Although TRE can look
strange, the reflex mechanism

00:48:54.160 --> 00:48:58.120 align:middle line:10%
allows the body to unwind
trapped muscle tension

00:48:58.120 --> 00:49:01.220 align:middle line:10%
and to calm itself
naturally, without words

00:49:01.220 --> 00:49:02.350 align:middle line:10%
or conscious effort.

00:49:02.350 --> 00:49:06.760 align:middle line:90%


00:49:06.760 --> 00:49:09.950 align:middle line:84%
TRE can be taught in
groups or individually.

00:49:09.950 --> 00:49:20.070 align:middle line:90%


00:49:20.070 --> 00:49:23.200 align:middle line:10%
Our ability to shake
off stress, including

00:49:23.200 --> 00:49:28.300 align:middle line:10%
unconscious traumatic stress,
may be hardwired in our brain.

00:49:28.300 --> 00:49:32.720 align:middle line:10%
Our capacity to be calmed by
rhythmic motion or vibration

00:49:32.720 --> 00:49:36.360 align:middle line:10%
can be observed even from birth.

00:49:36.360 --> 00:49:38.640 align:middle line:10%
Without any prompting,
parents seem

00:49:38.640 --> 00:49:42.620 align:middle line:10%
to know intuitively that
a gentle, bouncing motion

00:49:42.620 --> 00:49:46.220 align:middle line:10%
before rocking will lull an
infant into a calmer, relaxed

00:49:46.220 --> 00:49:46.720 align:middle line:10%
state.

00:49:46.720 --> 00:49:52.820 align:middle line:90%


00:49:52.820 --> 00:49:57.070 align:middle line:10%
A few of the reported
benefits are better sleep

00:49:57.070 --> 00:50:03.380 align:middle line:10%
and clearer thinking, reduced
levels of stress and anxiety,

00:50:03.380 --> 00:50:08.360 align:middle line:10%
reduced muscle tension and back
pain, reduced levels of worry

00:50:08.360 --> 00:50:11.470 align:middle line:10%
when burdened by
chronic illness,

00:50:11.470 --> 00:50:16.280 align:middle line:10%
reduced anger and reduced
over-reactivity, better

00:50:16.280 --> 00:50:21.010 align:middle line:10%
relationships both with
coworkers and family, greater

00:50:21.010 --> 00:50:23.250 align:middle line:10%
resiliency and
feelings of optimism.

00:50:23.250 --> 00:50:28.590 align:middle line:90%


00:50:28.590 --> 00:50:31.340 align:middle line:10%
The scientific nature
and healing potential

00:50:31.340 --> 00:50:33.820 align:middle line:10%
of this tension-releasing
mechanism

00:50:33.820 --> 00:50:36.280 align:middle line:10%
is only partially understood.

00:50:36.280 --> 00:50:40.380 align:middle line:10%
More research is
needed and continues.

00:50:40.380 --> 00:50:43.840 align:middle line:10%
The Department of
Defense DCOE lists

00:50:43.840 --> 00:50:47.390 align:middle line:10%
TRE as a level III modality.

00:50:47.390 --> 00:50:49.840 align:middle line:84%
Evidence-based pilot
research projects

00:50:49.840 --> 00:50:53.576 align:middle line:84%
are underway in Europe, South
Africa, and North America.

00:50:53.576 --> 00:50:58.340 align:middle line:90%


00:50:58.340 --> 00:51:01.970 align:middle line:10%
Increasingly, TRE is
used by professionals

00:51:01.970 --> 00:51:05.860 align:middle line:10%
as a complementary intervention
to help restore balance

00:51:05.860 --> 00:51:08.447 align:middle line:10%
and optimism for those
dealing with the effects

00:51:08.447 --> 00:51:09.280 align:middle line:10%
of traumatic stress.

00:51:09.280 --> 00:51:16.910 align:middle line:90%


00:51:16.910 --> 00:51:19.760 align:middle line:84%
It is also being used
by thousands of people

00:51:19.760 --> 00:51:22.610 align:middle line:84%
around the world
as a self-help tool

00:51:22.610 --> 00:51:26.260 align:middle line:84%
to relieve stress and
tension, to sleep better,

00:51:26.260 --> 00:51:27.740 align:middle line:90%
or simply to feel good.

00:51:27.740 --> 00:51:34.240 align:middle line:90%


00:51:34.240 --> 00:51:38.050 align:middle line:84%
TRE has spread by
word-of-mouth and is now being

00:51:38.050 --> 00:51:41.370 align:middle line:90%
taught in over 35 countries.

00:51:41.370 --> 00:51:43.820 align:middle line:90%
