00:52:01.632 --> 00:52:03.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's
talk about that.

00:52:03.090 --> 00:52:05.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean, animals,
the animal kingdom,

00:52:05.240 --> 00:52:06.324 align:middle line:90%
does this quite naturally.

00:52:06.324 --> 00:52:06.990 align:middle line:90%
>>BERCELI: Yeah.

00:52:06.990 --> 00:52:10.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because they don't
have the mental resistance

00:52:10.840 --> 00:52:11.760 align:middle line:90%
that we have.

00:52:11.760 --> 00:52:12.610 align:middle line:90%
>>BERCELI: Right.

00:52:12.610 --> 00:52:15.970 align:middle line:84%
Peter Levine was one of the
people who first really, sort

00:52:15.970 --> 00:52:19.030 align:middle line:84%
of, brought this to
our social conscious--

00:52:19.030 --> 00:52:21.300 align:middle line:84%
is that animals
naturally tremor.

00:52:21.300 --> 00:52:23.950 align:middle line:84%
You can see your dog tremoring
during a thunderstorm

00:52:23.950 --> 00:52:25.910 align:middle line:84%
or after they've
been in an accident.

00:52:25.910 --> 00:52:28.450 align:middle line:84%
If you see a horse
fall, when it gets up,

00:52:28.450 --> 00:52:30.030 align:middle line:90%
it shakes all over its body.

00:52:30.030 --> 00:52:32.610 align:middle line:84%
It may tremor even for half
an hour, as an example.

00:52:32.610 --> 00:52:35.260 align:middle line:84%
Animals don't have the
blockage that we have.

00:52:35.260 --> 00:52:36.760 align:middle line:90%
They're more instinctual.

00:52:36.760 --> 00:52:40.510 align:middle line:84%
And so what happens when an
animal injures itself or it get

00:52:40.510 --> 00:52:42.820 align:middle line:84%
anxious or nervous,
it automatically

00:52:42.820 --> 00:52:45.030 align:middle line:84%
begins to tremor
all over the body.

00:52:45.030 --> 00:52:47.880 align:middle line:84%
And that's actually the
nervous system trying

00:52:47.880 --> 00:52:49.640 align:middle line:90%
to calm down the organism.

00:52:49.640 --> 00:52:51.360 align:middle line:84%
And as a result of
that, there's a book

00:52:51.360 --> 00:52:54.410 align:middle line:84%
called "Why Zebras
Don't get Ulcers."

00:52:54.410 --> 00:52:56.890 align:middle line:84%
And that's because they
complete the cycle.

00:52:56.890 --> 00:53:00.610 align:middle line:84%
Animals live in life-or-death
threats in the wild every day.

00:53:00.610 --> 00:53:03.360 align:middle line:84%
But they don't have Post
Traumatic Stress Disorder.

00:53:03.360 --> 00:53:05.470 align:middle line:90%
See, only humans have that one.

00:53:05.470 --> 00:53:07.780 align:middle line:84%
And some domesticated
animals demonstrate

00:53:07.780 --> 00:53:10.576 align:middle line:84%
Post Traumatic Stress Disorder
but not animals in the wild.

00:53:10.576 --> 00:53:11.492 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:53:11.492 --> 00:53:13.759 align:middle line:84%
Because they're too tied
to the human species.

00:53:13.759 --> 00:53:14.800 align:middle line:90%
>>BERCELI: Exactly right.

00:53:14.800 --> 00:53:16.990 align:middle line:84%
Exactly right,
and we limit them.

00:53:16.990 --> 00:53:22.030 align:middle line:84%
But in our natural
state, the nervous system

00:53:22.030 --> 00:53:24.240 align:middle line:84%
would become aroused
during the traumatic event.

00:53:24.240 --> 00:53:25.740 align:middle line:84%
After the traumatic
event is over,

00:53:25.740 --> 00:53:27.530 align:middle line:84%
the body begins
to tremor itself.

00:53:27.530 --> 00:53:30.660 align:middle line:84%
It brings yourself back into
a para-sympathetic response,

00:53:30.660 --> 00:53:31.640 align:middle line:90%
and it's over.

00:53:31.640 --> 00:53:34.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we're seeing it
as it should be in nature.

00:53:34.040 --> 00:53:34.790 align:middle line:90%
>>BERCELI: Mm-hmm.

00:53:34.790 --> 00:53:36.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, particularly
vulnerable groups--

00:53:36.860 --> 00:53:40.470 align:middle line:84%
aside from people coming
back from war situations--

00:53:40.470 --> 00:53:41.452 align:middle line:90%
are women and children.

00:53:41.452 --> 00:53:42.160 align:middle line:90%
>>BERCELI: Right.

00:53:42.160 --> 00:53:43.632 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's
true globally.

00:53:43.632 --> 00:53:44.840 align:middle line:90%
>>BERCELI: Right, absolutely.

00:53:44.840 --> 00:53:45.340 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:53:45.340 --> 00:53:47.120 align:middle line:84%
Now, what I do--
which is really great.

00:53:47.120 --> 00:53:49.780 align:middle line:84%
And this is women and children
just in life in general,

00:53:49.780 --> 00:53:51.780 align:middle line:90%
in our society actually.

00:53:51.780 --> 00:53:56.200 align:middle line:84%
And mothers in particular
who are single mothers that

00:53:56.200 --> 00:53:59.640 align:middle line:84%
have several children--
they're highly stressed lives.

00:53:59.640 --> 00:54:03.470 align:middle line:84%
I teach mothers all the time
how to do this for themselves

00:54:03.470 --> 00:54:04.090 align:middle line:90%
first.

00:54:04.090 --> 00:54:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Because every child is
regulating, unconsciously,

00:54:07.510 --> 00:54:09.280 align:middle line:90%
to the mother's nervous system.

00:54:09.280 --> 00:54:12.860 align:middle line:84%
All the children from very
young aged into teenage

00:54:12.860 --> 00:54:15.010 align:middle line:90%
know when the mother is upset.

00:54:15.010 --> 00:54:17.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's not the face
or the eyes or anything.

00:54:17.860 --> 00:54:19.510 align:middle line:84%
It's picking up on
the nervous system.

00:54:19.510 --> 00:54:21.280 align:middle line:84%
Because all our nervous
systems generally

00:54:21.280 --> 00:54:22.780 align:middle line:90%
regulate towards each other.

00:54:22.780 --> 00:54:24.470 align:middle line:84%
It's a safety thing
that happens to us

00:54:24.470 --> 00:54:26.740 align:middle line:84%
unconsciously to test
out whether there's

00:54:26.740 --> 00:54:28.300 align:middle line:90%
safety or danger here.

00:54:28.300 --> 00:54:32.090 align:middle line:84%
And so, mothers need to calm
down first and get themselves

00:54:32.090 --> 00:54:34.780 align:middle line:84%
in a state of homeostasis
or more calmness.

00:54:34.780 --> 00:54:37.506 align:middle line:84%
And the children will
automatically follow them, see?

00:54:37.506 --> 00:54:38.382 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:54:38.382 --> 00:54:40.340 align:middle line:84%
>>BERCELI: But then the
mothers, they're great.

00:54:40.340 --> 00:54:42.589 align:middle line:84%
If they have a good relationship
with their children--

00:54:42.589 --> 00:54:45.260 align:middle line:84%
I teach this to mothers all the
time-- they lay on the floor.

00:54:45.260 --> 00:54:47.430 align:middle line:90%
They play with the children.

00:54:47.430 --> 00:54:49.570 align:middle line:84%
They do shake
together all the time.

00:54:49.570 --> 00:54:51.200 align:middle line:90%
The children laugh and giggle.

00:54:51.200 --> 00:54:52.944 align:middle line:90%
And it becomes a playful event.

00:54:52.944 --> 00:54:54.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
what a wonderful--

00:54:54.360 --> 00:54:55.090 align:middle line:84%
>>BERCELI: And the
children love it.

00:54:55.090 --> 00:54:56.280 align:middle line:90%
It makes them feel better.

00:54:56.280 --> 00:54:58.056 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:54:58.056 --> 00:54:59.430 align:middle line:84%
We just have a
minute or so left.

00:54:59.430 --> 00:55:01.670 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about forgiveness
and how forgiveness

00:55:01.670 --> 00:55:02.757 align:middle line:90%
plays into all of this.

00:55:02.757 --> 00:55:03.340 align:middle line:90%
>>BERCELI: OK.

00:55:03.340 --> 00:55:05.450 align:middle line:84%
Forgiveness is a very
complicated thing.

00:55:05.450 --> 00:55:09.470 align:middle line:84%
Because some traumas
are vindictive.

00:55:09.470 --> 00:55:11.740 align:middle line:84%
If somebody beats you
up, different from you're

00:55:11.740 --> 00:55:16.160 align:middle line:84%
in an earthquake where it's
from God or whatever, nature,

00:55:16.160 --> 00:55:17.030 align:middle line:90%
that sort of thing.

00:55:17.030 --> 00:55:19.704 align:middle line:84%
And so, that plays
a role in about how

00:55:19.704 --> 00:55:20.620 align:middle line:90%
we're able to forgive.

00:55:20.620 --> 00:55:21.700 align:middle line:90%
Do I have to forgive God?

00:55:21.700 --> 00:55:22.970 align:middle line:90%
Or do I have to forgive you?

00:55:22.970 --> 00:55:25.760 align:middle line:84%
Or do I have to
forgive my spouse?

00:55:25.760 --> 00:55:27.220 align:middle line:90%
--or et cetera.

00:55:27.220 --> 00:55:31.220 align:middle line:10%
Forgiveness, at its deepest
level-- I truly believe,

00:55:31.220 --> 00:55:33.180 align:middle line:10%
when people have
gone through trauma

00:55:33.180 --> 00:55:35.340 align:middle line:10%
and really tried
to resolve it-- is

00:55:35.340 --> 00:55:40.700 align:middle line:10%
we end up forgiving us
that we are this way.

00:55:40.700 --> 00:55:43.070 align:middle line:84%
It's not a vindictive
directed thing.

00:55:43.070 --> 00:55:44.660 align:middle line:84%
And it's not, you
have to forgive me.

00:55:44.660 --> 00:55:46.140 align:middle line:90%
Or I have to forgive you.

00:55:46.140 --> 00:55:49.390 align:middle line:84%
We have to experience
that we as a human species

00:55:49.390 --> 00:55:53.070 align:middle line:84%
have to forgive ourselves
for being the way we are.

00:55:53.070 --> 00:55:56.030 align:middle line:84%
And that is the most
profound level of forgiveness

00:55:56.030 --> 00:55:57.010 align:middle line:90%
I think I've ever seen.

00:55:57.010 --> 00:55:57.885 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:55:57.885 --> 00:56:00.820 align:middle line:84%
And finally, is it
advisable then--

00:56:00.820 --> 00:56:02.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it sounds
like it for, really,

00:56:02.680 --> 00:56:05.010 align:middle line:84%
pretty much anybody that's
living in the modern world.

00:56:05.010 --> 00:56:08.320 align:middle line:84%
Because we are being conditioned
towards stress and trauma

00:56:08.320 --> 00:56:11.110 align:middle line:84%
all the time, subconsciously,
and as you said,

00:56:11.110 --> 00:56:12.590 align:middle line:90%
